---
title: Roasted Red Pepper & Feta Burgers with Roasted Potato Wedges
description: The classic combo of feta cheese and roasted red peppers strikes again! This time, they’ve teamed up to create the Mediterranean-style burger you didn't know you needed. Patties are infused with garlic, tangy Dijon, and creamy feta, then seared and sandwiched between toasted buns. A roasted red pepper spread is slathered inside, then everything’s finished with more feta and served with potato wedges on the side. Roasted red peppa + feta foreva!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/roasted-red-pepper-feta-burgers-964d28ef.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/roasted-red-pepper-feta-burgers-628c06154edbcd81ae0801a4-e98d61c9.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 850 kcal
  fat: 41 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 81 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1510 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/roasted-red-pepper-and-feta-burgers-628c06154edbcd81ae0801a4
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Mediterranean
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve @potato buns{2}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, half the @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and @pepper{}.

> Crumble feta into smaller pieces for easier combining.

Form into two patties (four for 4), each slightly wider than a burger bun.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

While burgers cook, toast buns directly on oven rack until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Spread bottom buns with half the @roasted red pepper spread{4%ounce}. Fill buns with patties, remaining roasted red pepper spread, and remaining feta.

Serve with potato wedges on the side.